defaultAdopting a rights-based approach, we recognise that a person is disabled by the attitudinal, institutional and environmen
defaulttal barriers they face within society and therefore addressing these barriers is a means to achieving equality. Through our work, we highlight and address the additional and 
defaultspecific barriers that disabled children and their families face. 
